    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-05-02T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-05-02T10:00:00-05:00" n="283"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">362.1163 Watch Tower/8: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Berlin (<persName type="from"
                            >Messersmith</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-02T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 2, 1933—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 2—11:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to the Department’s telegram No. 46, April 27, 6 p.m., to the Embassy,
                    I am able to report Watch Tower Society premises again free and Society
                    functioning through the good offices of the Consulate General.</p>
                <p>Full report by mail my despatch No. 1269.<note n="55" xml:id="d283fn55">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Messersmith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
